    "The general objective is to ensure that the predicted label of the corresponding augmented case aligns with the pseudo-labels.",
    "In this way, the vast amount of unlabeled cases is leveraged as well to optimize the prediction of y.",
    "The minimization of both supervised loss (L s) and unsupervised loss (L u) is hindered by the imbalanced distribution of classes in y.",
    "Specifically, the 'maybe' class is significantly underrepresented compared to the 'yes' and 'no' classes.",
    "This imbalance is further aggravated when combined with an automatically annotated dataset that only includes 'yes' or 'no' labels."
